text: Check it out: GSS Sec. @eeighan live tweets Board meeting about the Rec Center with her own reactions to public comment session.
What I love about working in ed? The energy. Listen to a grad student talk about their project; the enthusiasm is infectious. #LoveEducation
Fee hearing went very well. With only a $3 fee increase (the first since '99!) GSS will be able keep doing the things you love us for.
1st meeting of the semester is tomorrow night in our great new permanent space, Whetten 200. Democracy! Pizza! Join us!
Our grad trustee Rose Barham was featured on UConn Today! http://t.co/TICcfjYX
Something I really could have used as a new grad student: http://t.co/axPpzwy0 #gradchat

GSS knows what you're all about: good times, jobs, dancing all night. In that order. Well, chronologically. Check out our upcoming FB events
Hi Erin. NAGPS's account got hacked, apparently.  Ours is fine as far as I know.
SU Grad Lounge renovations have funding! Huge thanks to Student Activities and the Grad School. Expect to see changes soon!
Do you park in Area 3? Important winter break info: http://t.co/vyrLNIqK
@SU_GSO Hey, grad solidarity, right? Closing out a busy semester as usual.
Just finished the last GSS of the semester. Many thanks to the hardest working Exec board in the business. Have a great break, everyone!
Creativity break! After a day of GSS-related meetings, I'm reading a short fiction piece at Long River Live in CLAS/Austin tonight at 7:30.
Lunch w/ Provost candidate & USG rep: free quiche AND a chance to brag about what makes #UConn great? Amazing morning.
Three free meals in one day = grad student bingo. I almost achieved that yesterday.
RT @USATODAYcollege: Great infographic on whether grad school is really worth the money - http://t.co/DEUd3ETJ
We served Thanksgiving Dinner to over 650 hungry, happy grads. Thanks to Anish, Bing, and all the volunteers for making it rock so hard.
A little snow day can't stop democracy! Join us and Grad School Assoc. Dean Chafouleas for the rescheduled senate meeting Wednesday.
It's not too late to get in on AcWriMo and set big writing goals this month. Check out  resources on PhD 2 Published. http://t.co/NF0ZN4m9.
Just got approved to have the GSS Professional Development Symposium reception at the Benton. It's going to be swanky! Thanks, Ally Walton.
GSS is snowed-out tonight. And I was so excited to talk about grad handbooks, SU lounge renovation plans, and our sweet NEW MEETING SPACE.
Today's tweet brought to you by...democracy. I was happy to see grad student faces at the Willimantic polling center.
Harvard post-grad career pro Melanie Sinche agreed to give the keynote at the GSS Professional Development Symposium. I'm already excited!
RT @GradShare: "10 Great Twitter Chats for Grad Students" Nice list from @dailymuse! http://t.co/Fk6dqIAN
Curled up in Benton cafe listening to the Ghostbusters theme and very content with my latte. I envision a grad social space here someday.
GSS senators making the news! http://t.co/rcjm742l
Just came from GSS breakfast with Pres. Herbst and my first dissertation chapter conference. What an action-packed morning!
Who's the man? VP/CFO Rich Gray--UConn admin superstar--will talk at GSS tonight. And, a leave policy that won't stigmatize pregnant grads?
Just set up a meeting with CT Rides to talk about carpooling. If you carpool or want to, you're the expert! Send your questions my way.

Do you know a grad alum who works outside academia? Put us in touch, we want to invite them to the Professional Development Symposium!
If you're a senator, RSVP for Breakfast with Pres. Herbst on 10/25! If not, talk to your dept.'s senator. If they're not going, you should!
Invitations are out to GSS senators and friends for Breakfast w/ Pres. Herbst 10/25. Be sure your senator RSVPs for 1 of 15 remaining seats!
What elements would you want to see in a university-wide orientation for all new grad students?
Great meeting! Love goes out to Sen. Virga and Sen. Tomchek for volunteering as reps on IT Governance and Mansfield Downtown Partnership.

New Interim Provost Choi will be at GSS tonight! Come have pizza with the Provost and let's talk about the academic future of UConn.
Talked to Pres. Herbst this morning about grad student parking. Let it not be said that I am afraid to annoy people in high places.
Looking into how CT Rides (http://t.co/bW4I8DHD) vanpool and NuRide carpool program might help grads. Share your ideas and experiences!

WRTD is on the mend! Parking still troubling but solutions are coming (Zimride carpooling, Mansfield garage). Commuters, try F and I-lot.
VP Safet Berisa and I spent this morning networking w/ Pres. Herbst, grad trustee Rose Barham, and undergrad student leaders over breakfast.
I'm unreasonably excited about our new GSS grad student blog, created by Secretary Erin Eighan and the PR Committee. http://t.co/z8fejIou.
What would you like to see in your SU grad student lounge? TV? Fridge? Coffee maker? Send ideas and help us create a renovation plan.
Got UConn parking or WRTD bus problems? Tell me about them before my big meeting w/ parking/transportation admin next Wednesday.
Randy's Pizza at GSS tonight, thanks to Anish's negotiation skills and excellent (meaning coinciding with mine) taste in pizza.
RT @UConnCLAS: Stanley Fish, higher ed pundit, said in a UConn talk that professors take academic freedom too far. http://t.co/YeB4cRxq  ...
GSS tonight CLAS 163 7-9. I'll be there, despite nuclear sunburn. Will GSS get a real meeting space? What's up w/ maternity leave? Find out.
Just put a grad rep on the Provost's Commission for Institutional Diversity. Big things are happening in diversity at UConn this year!
Spent two hours at the EGSA voter registration table outside the library and got sunburned. They're open until 5--go register!
Spent a few hours grading while emails piled up, felt like I was cheating on GSS. I kept checking my GSS inbox like, "Soon, my love, soon."
RT @GradShare: "As Your Academic Clock is Ticking, Are Student-Run Journals Worth The Time?" guest blog by Nina Flores http://t.co/VHeKHtZl
I love getting passionate people on committees that matter. Working to revise the grad maternity leave policy. http://t.co/5PABQ7HP.
